# LLM calls: single gate (no bypass)

**Required architecture:**

```text
pipeline / feature code
   → safe_llm_call()          # src/ops/llm_client.py — only approved doorway
   → assert_llm_call_allowed()   # BEFORE any network I/O (budget / dry-run / caps)
   → vendor API call           # OpenAI / Anthropic / … ONLY inside llm_client
   → record_llm_usage()        # AFTER response — prefer API-reported tokens & cost
```

**Forbidden:**

```text
pipeline code → vendor SDK directly
```

If any file can reach the API without going through `safe_llm_call`, it can bypass the guard.

**Policy:** No raw vendor calls anywhere except inside the approved `llm_client` wrapper.

**Estimates vs reality:** `estimate_tokens()` in `cost_guard` is a coarse heuristic (chars÷4) for pre-flight budgets. Stronger protection later uses the **tokenizer for the target model**. After each real call, **`record_llm_usage`** must be fed **actual** input/output tokens and **actual** billed cost from the API when available—not estimates alone.
